article.description: — Noah Thomasson scored 24 points as Niagara beat Quinnipiac 64-60 on Sunday.
article.headline: Niagara earns 64-60 win over Quinnipiac
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- — Noah Thomasson scored 24 points as Niagara beat Quinnipiac 64-60 on Sunday. Thomasson added five assists for the Purple Eagles (4-4). Aaron Gray scored 14 points and added nine rebounds. Lance Erving finished with eight points. Tyrese Williams finished with 18 points for the Bobcats (7-2). Ike Nweke added 15 points and nine rebounds for Quinnipiac. Dezi Jones put up 12 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
